here are a few comments on this video, including mine. it seems that i wasn't the only one who didn't exactly agree. https://t.co/LNMcPMaqMQ

however, this video does not measure up to those he's made in the past. it feels like less research combined with more fancy graphics and editing. it feels like a rough draft with beautiful formatting. it feels unpolished.

johnny works hard to put difficult ideas into simple language. he has two million subscribers. i think that many of his videos are incredible, and i don't want this to be a huge rant about johnny's ability to effectively analyze conflict. please don't take it that way.

i'm not here to say that putin couldn't have thought about it this way...but THERE'S SO MUCH THAT'S BEEN LEFT OUT, for example, the economic connections between these two countries (in addition to other countries in eastern europe).

he spends a large part of that video analyzing putin's blog post and calling him a romantic. he basically outright says that putin is blindly going after ukraine to reunite it with russia, because putin thinks they have an almost familial connection.

my standards for video journalism are quite low, to be honest. geopolitical commentary requires a LOT of research. i don't want to undermine johnny's efforts here, but there's something that really needs to be addressed here:
his take sucks.
